<br>
Back when Hate first opened they had a huge Dark elf invasion in Kithicore and Rivervale. A lot of people werent happy when they logged on and were killed in the &quot;safehaven&quot; of Rivervale by Dark elf invaders. Several times in some cases before they were wise enough to turn off EQ.<br>
<br>
The design of the newbie lands and bind points dont make for a very efficient means to allow an &quot;Invasion&quot; without pissing off whom ever is bound there. No matter how much advance notice you give, someone will miss the news. Hell people dont even read patch info. How many times have you had some illiterate asking in game about a change on patch day that was clearly discussed by the patch message?<br>
<br>
The solution is to talk all you want about conquering the world and understanding that in the scope of the game it wont happen.<br>
<br>
The history is there, just remember you cant make it do anything in the future. Use it to create your story realizing that while you make the story it cant effect the future in any meaningful way except within the realm of the scope of your character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 932<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 1:50:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Actually, I was thinking more about ..</span><hr size=1> .. GM events and such than about particular quests.  On the event side, nothing that has ever happened in the past really has much relevance to what is happening in the event.  This is true even for events that supposedly &quot;advance the plot&quot;.  What those events typically do is just provide a plot device to explain whatever change VI decided to implement.<br>
<br>
In the case of classic RP, the story (RP) is the dog and the game-play is the tail -- the dog wags the tail (story drives the action).  In EQ, the tail wags the dog. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukreelosthehunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreelos the Hunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 349<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 3:08:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I was the original poster</span><hr size=1> My concern was that people do not have a cohesive backstory to set their personal backgrounds against.<br>
<br>
One of my biggest questions are whether Half-Elves are sterile.  I think I've seen some indication they are not in the game but I'm still not sure.<br>
<br>
Most races all start in one set place.  Why?  Game design or xenophobia?<br>
<br>
Are there Dark Elves who advocate peace with the other elves or is that sedition for which they would be put to death?<br>
<br>
How are good and evil defined in the world?<br>
<br>
These are the kind of questions the cause stumbling blocks for interaction in an RP environement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarthur265.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arthur265</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 4:22:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I was the original poster</span><hr size=1> Why should an entire world have a cohessive story?  It should for the most part appear to be pieces of stories here and there.  Only the most seasoned and well traveled veterans might see some sort of big picture.<br>
<br>
I think that guy who put that big 'war of the gods' picture together was really on to something.  Even if he wasn't all right, so what?  It's still great fiction, and there's definitely more to come.<br>
<br>
Also, Enedlithien hit it on the head when she said that the EQ writers have to unravel the story slowly to give players the chance to participate in it.  If some new quest appears which is some new piece of the big picture it'll take a while for players to do it and catch on.  After that they might take the next step with the story.<br>
<br>
As for the game being too static, it's for the previous reason that we need to be a bit patient.  However, you can just go along with some part of the story line or make one up, and go with it.  Iksar can go ahead and battle for control of Norrath.  Empires weren't built in a day.  It could be that you'll wake up one day and find an Iksar camp on Faydwer.  Who knows?<br>
<br>
The point is there is a story.  It just unravels slowly. <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421">Trevian</A><br>
