<br>
This was taken from the pages of the EQ RPG published by White Wolf last month. So apparently half elves aren't sterile.<br>
<br>
But a few points must be considered here. VI has done a terrible job of presenting material for players to make back stories. Are dark elves inherently evil or is cultural? How do young gnomes get recruited into necromancy? What code, if any, do paladins follow? Normally I wouldn't even attempt to build a character in a pen and paper RPG on the scant information a new player can find about Norrath.<br>
<br>
How much do you officialy know about your race? How much did you know the first day you started playing? Do you know who governs your toon's hometown? Do you know how to find out? Your toon's race's lifespan? When did your toon reach adulthood? So many basics have been left out.<br>
<br>
I also have to agree, EQs stories have come to a standstill. Or at least that's partially correct. New zones might add to the story, but I doubt Sony will do anything to move any of the old stories along. <br>
<br>
It wouldn't be impossible to have the militia take over North Freeport. Move all the NPCs connected to the temple to an outpost somewhere (a change to Ro, or add a zone off of Ro). Anyone who was bound in North Freeport would now be bound where ever the temple was moved to. Yes, this would take a little work, but that is what the game is supposed to be like.<br>
<br>
If VI had been changing their world more often, we would have gotten used to it by now, and learned to look out for potenial political changes. This would have added a new dimension to the game.<br>
