<br>
I do NOT and never have, liked the idea that we(Teir'dal) were created evil and thats just how it is. I want a reason to hate, a reason to be twisted, greater than I just can't help it.<br>
<br>
Some of the history implies that the Teir'dal left the combine empire, and turned on the others because they other races, non dark, could not tolerate the 'evil' crafts like necromancy.<br>
<br>
In any case, what I create out of the mess of verants history will be to liven things up, and to give my characters a unique perspective. I think the official story of any game should never assert THIS is the exact truth when speaking towards mystical things, gods or magics. It adds so much when there are rumors, or information that you have interpet and use. I like gradual disclosure and plot twists, in my 'history'.<br>
<br>
